text: RT McConnell: “If this election were overturned by mere allegations from the losing side, our democracy would enter a death spiral.”
name: Dwight Evans

text: I know my office has received several calls asking if I’m safe. I am. I ask for your prayers & thoughts for the police who are working to restore a safe environment inside the People’s House, the Capitol.
name: Dwight Evans

name: Dwight Evans

name: Dwight Evans

text: This is a blatant attack on American democracy. We will have a transfer of power on January 20th, and Joe Biden and Kamala Harris will become President and Vice President on that day. American democracy has survived over 200 years, and it will survive Donald Trump.
name: John Garamendi

text: RT We will reconvene. We will vote to accept the electors from the states, as instructed by the Constitution. That is our job. #StandUpForAmerica To those storming the Capitol - I am on the House floor and I will not be deterred from upholding my oath, under God, to the Constitution by mob demand. #StandUpForAmerica
name: Mike Lee

text: The violence at the United States Capitol is completely unacceptable. It is time for the protesters to disperse.My staff and I are safe. We are working to finish our constitutional duty to finish counting votes today.God bless the Capitol Police keeping us all safe.
name: Mike Lee

text: Whether we get back in the chamber or convene in a different location, the Senate should continue the work of the American people immediately. This outrage cannot be allowed to disrupt that work for a minute longer.

text: Congress was elected to govern. We need to get back on the floor and gavel in the Senate as soon as possible.
name: Mike Lee

text: My staff and I are safe. Thank you to everyone who has reached out. An incredibly sad day for our republic.

text: RT Arrest this man.
name: Bennie Thompson

text: Have you said this to my colleagues in the delegation?
name: Bennie Thompson

text: I am safe. Thank you for your prayers!

text: These thugs have no respect for our democracy.
name: Bennie Thompson

text: I will vote to certify the November Presidential Election. The people have spoken!

text: RT This is what (D-VA) told me yesterday:Republicans “are inciting violence. Trump is too."“Now the counting of ballots, which is a ministerial act, is now going to become an opportunity for political incitement and potential violence.”
name: Gerry Connolly

text: Trump incited this. He urged the Proud Boys to show up today in a barely veiled invite to disrupt the count. You'd be blind to not see this coming. And now it's time to end it
name: Gerry Connolly

text: I am safe and raring to get back to the electoral ballot count. We will not be deterred by bully tactics, violence, or "alternative facts." Today, truth and democracy WILL prevail.
name: Gerry Connolly

text: What has Trump wrought? The Capitol stormed. House and Senate chambers evacuated. Gas masks issued. Counting of electoral ballots disrupted. Democracy at the edge. Enough, America. Enough.
name: Gerry Connolly

text: We’ve been given gas masks on the House floor. Tear gas has been used in the Rotunda.
name: Gerry Connolly

text: House Chamber has been warned to be prepared to shelter in place due to breach of Capitol Rotunda. Surreal.
name: Gerry Connolly

text: The US Capitol is breached and in lockdown. This is the chaos sown by Trump and his enablers. I am seeing this through. Violence and intimidation can not prevail in a democracy.
name: Gerry Connolly

text: I'm safe, sheltering in a secure place, and listening to the guidance of law enforcement. Thank you to the Capitol Police and law enforcement for keeping everyone safe.
name: Debbie Stabenow

text: Here’s a short video I recorded commenting on what occurred today here at the Capitol.
name: Robert Aderholt

text: God has brought this nation through many dark days over the past 240 plus years. We have always been able to settle our disputes peaceably. I believe He will continue to guide & protect this nation. However, as a nation we need to see His guidance in peace. He is in full control!
name: Robert Aderholt

text: I was on the House Floor this afternoon objecting to the electoral votes with many of my colleagues. We had to evacuate due to a security breach. I ask for your prayers during this time in our nation's history.
name: Robert Aderholt

text: We have a constitutional right to peaceful protests but the clashes with police and destruction of property must stop now. We can disagree in a better way.
name: Mike Simpson

text: These were not protesters, they are rioters they are terrorists. NBC News: Addressing the reports of IEDs found near the Capitol the FBI says, “two suspected explosive devices were rendered safe by the FBI and our law enforcement partners. The investigation is ongoing.”Reported by Mike Kosnar.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: I have signed onto my colleague 's resolution. Any House members who have tried to overturn the election and install a dictatorship have violated the Constitution and should not sit in Congress. I believe the Republican members of Congress who have incited this domestic terror attack through their attempts to overturn the election must face consequences. They have broken their sacred Oath of Office. I will be introducing a resolution calling for their expulsion.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: When he leaves office trump must be prosecuted for his crimes, including his incitement to violence. Liz Cheney is on NBC right now saying that President Trump is responsible for inciting the violent occupation of the Capitol. Liz Cheney!
name: Bill Pascrell

text: This authoritarianism will not disappear in 14 days. I have been calling for accountability for four years. It cannot be ignored any longer. The long-term preservation of democracy is in our hands right now. It is the challenge of our time to eradicate this poison starting now.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: To all the trump sycophants who followed his cues, to all my gop colleagues I say this: once the fascist genie is out of the bottle, he can’t be put back in.Violent fascism at our doorstep was fed by republicans fomenting extremism against our govt for years. They built this.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: When he leaves office trump must be prosecuted for his crimes, perhaps including his incitement to violence. If the Defense Dept blocked the deployment of the National Guard, any one responsible for that must be held accountable and possibly arrested.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: Today inside the Capitol republicans sought to tear down our democracy while the rightwing extremist mob they whipped up outside is violently trying to do the same.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: This attempted coup is treasonous, incited directly by donald trump and some congressional republicans.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: Joe Biden will be officially certified by us. I promise you. Hakeem Jeffries says members plan to return and certify the Electoral College. Members from both parties applaud.But first, they’re still clearing the Capitol.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: If we don’t confront the violent fascism at our doorstep right now it will only grow. If they get away with this it will be worse next time. I promise you.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: I was on the floor but I am safe with my brave staff. What we are witnessing is an attempted coup directly incited by the criminal in the White House. It will fail.
name: Bill Pascrell

text: Every American should watch what is happening on the steps of the Capitol as rightwing mobs attack police while here inside republicans try to overturn the election. The two are complementary attacks on democracy.Thank you to brave Capitol Police for keeping all of us safe. Whoa: Trump supporters going at it with the police on the steps of the Capitol as Congress counts the Electoral College ballots inside
name: Bill Pascrell

text: Order will be restored.Congress will do its job. This election will be certified, and Joe Biden will, as he was duly elected to do, take office as our next President on January 20th.
name: Adam Smith

text: They do not believe in democracy. They believe in retaining power by any means necessary. All Americans who believe in the rule of law and our Constitution must clearly and unambiguously hold these people accountable for their actions.
name: Adam Smith

text: President Trump and his enablers are directly responsible for the despicable acts at our nation's Capitol that we all have witnessed today. The President incited and encouraged this riot. He has lied repeatedly, as have his enablers in Congress and elsewhere about this election.
name: Adam Smith

text: I have spoken with Department of the Defense leadership who are now working with the DC government, the Dept. of Justice, and Capitol police to restore order to the Capitol and allow Members of Congress to safely certify the election results, as is our constitutional obligation.
name: Adam Smith

text: The assault by pro-Trump extremists on the United States Capitol is a criminal act aimed at ending our democracy as we know it.The Capitol campus must be cleared of these extremists as soon and as safely as possible.
name: Adam Smith

text: My staff and I are safe. This attempted coup and domestic terrorist attack needs to end immediately.
name: Adam Smith

text: We will not be intimidated. Congress will return to the House floor and resume certifying our election results. Democracy will prevail. BREAKING: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi says lawmakers will resume the certification of President-elect Joe Biden's win tonight once the Capitol is "cleared for use"
name: Mike Quigley

text: As soon as the House floor is clear, we WILL continue the business of democracy. We will certify Joe Biden and Kamala Harris as the next President and Vice-President.
name: Mike Quigley

text: I want to be clear: while this clear act of domestic terrorism may have succeeded in delaying proceedings today, Joe Biden will be sworn in as President on January 20.
name: Mike Quigley

text: Make no mistake: President Trump and his enablers are personally responsible for inciting this violence and he must immediately and unequivocally condemn it and urge his followers to stand down.
name: Mike Quigley

text: I want to thank the US Capitol Police for keeping us safe today. I was on the floor of the House earlier today and was evacuated. My staff and I are currently safe and continuing to follow instructions from USCP.
name: Mike Quigley

text: I am appalled at what is occurring in the US Capitol right now. President Trump needs to call for an end to this violence and permit Congress to facilitate a peaceful transition of power.
name: Mike Turner

text: Thankful for the Capitol Police, who are putting themselves in danger right now to protect the Capitol, Members, & staff. This is on the hands of Pres. Trump, Sen Cruz, & everyone of the so-called party of law & order who are encouraging chaos right now to overturn the election.
name: John B. Larson

text: The attack on the Capitol strikes at the most sacred act of our democracy: the peaceful transfer of power. It is an outrage and a threat to our most fundamental principles as a free people.
name: Tom McClintock

text: RT Electoral college ballots rescued from the Senate floor. If our capable floor staff hadn’t grabbed them, they would have been burned by the mob.
name: Sherrod Brown

text: My staff and I are safe.The violence at the Capitol needs to end now.The lives of countless workers – journalists, staff, and Capitol Police are being put at risk by this attack on our democracy.
name: Sherrod Brown

text: RT Thanks for all the texts and messages of concern. Just spoke with . They are currently locked in Senate chamber, but safe. I am struggling for the words right now.
name: Sherrod Brown

text: 2/2- In response to the many inquiries- I am thankful to the Capitol Police for maintaining order and security at our location. My staff and I are safe.
name: Lloyd Smucker

text: 1/2 - I am horrified by the violence and destruction at the Capitol. This is not who we are as a country. Please go home now.
name: Lloyd Smucker

text: Have faith. These terrorists will fail. They will be brought to justice. Their enablers will be brough to justice. If the President and his allies have any shred of honor left, they will tell these thugs to stand down now.
name: Jerrold Nadler

text: I am safe. We are sheltering in place. Make no mistake: President Trump and his enablers are directly responsible for this violence.

text: Political violence must not stop Congress from fulfilling its obligations. We will resume counting Electoral College votes as soon as possible.
name: Michael F. Doyle

text: I place the lion’s share of the blame for it on Donald Trump who incited a mob of supporters to carry it out.
name: Michael F. Doyle

text: The assault on the US Capitol today and the accompanying criminal violence, property destruction, and disruption of the People’s business was unacceptable and tragic. It’s contrary to all of our proud political traditions.
name: Michael F. Doyle

text: My staff and I are safe in a secure location. This violent attempt to overthrow our democratic process must stop.
name: Doris Matsui

text: Los individuos que irrumpieron en el Capitolio o atacaron a nuestros oficiales de la ley deben enfrentar las más severas consecuencias bajo la ley.
name: Mario Diaz-Balart

text: El Capitolio de EE. UU. es el centro y símbolo sagrado de la democracia. Las acciones violentas de hoy constituyen la mas inaceptable agresión contra los principios y valores que fundaron nuestra nación.
name: Mario Diaz-Balart

text: The Capitol building is the center and sacred symbol of democracy. Today’s violent actions undermine the principles and values that our nation was founded on.Individuals who broke into the US Capitol or assaulted our law enforcement should face the full consequences of the law.
name: Mario Diaz-Balart

text: We must protect and revere law our enforcement officers who put their lives on the line each day for our safety.While peaceful protests are an integral part of our democracy, lawlessness and violence are NOT acceptable.
name: Mario Diaz-Balart

text: My staff and I are currently safe and accounted for. Peaceful protest is fundamentally American, but violence must never be tolerated. I call on protestors to comply with Capitol Police, stand down, and leave the Capitol Building so that our Constitutional duties may resume.
name: Don Young

text: As an elected official, I take an oath of office to uphold the U.S. Constitution. The actions of our outgoing President today to unleash chaos mocks that oath. We are currently safe, but this is a disgraceful day for our country.
name: Brian Higgins

text: . is right – enough is enough. It’s past time for President Trump to simply accept that he lost the election and call off the mob. Congress will get back to certifying the election and ensuring that our democratic processes continue.
name: Frank Pallone

text: President Trump’s disdain for our democracy is in full view. The right to protest is a cornerstone of our democracy, but no one has the right to commit these heinous acts of violence just because they disagree with the outcome of an election.
name: Frank Pallone

text: I’m safe and currently under lockdown orders at the Capitol complex. I’ve never seen anything like this horrific attack but I want to assure you - we will carry out our constitutional duty and certify the results of the presidential election.
name: Frank Pallone

text: The House will return to business shortly. We will do our job, we will do what the constitution dictates and we will not let those who would tear down our democracy cause anything more than a pause in the proceedings.
name: Jim Himes

text: As I take off my gas mask and brush the glass shards from my knees, I’ll take too little too late for $1000, Alex. Violence is never the answer. What we see unfolding today in Washington D.C. is putting a black eye on our party and our Republic. The violence needs to stop and we need to all come together as Americans. “What unites us is far greater than what divides us”
name: Jim Himes

text: Police have asked us to get gas masks out as there has been tear gas used in the rotunda.
name: Jim Himes

text: Police have just told us to be prepared to get under our chairs in the chamber. They’ve placed guards in the galleries. Lieutenant advising us to be prepared to get behind our seats. There is no behind our seats.
name: Jim Himes

text: Instructions to people in the Capitol: remain silent.
name: Jim Himes

text: They just recessed the House. A lieutenant of the Capitol Police is now addressing us. Capitol building breached. Both chambers locked down.
name: Jim Himes

text: They’re locking the doors in the House chamber. Debate has stopped.
name: Jim Himes

text: This is the instruction being blasted out to all members of the United States Congress as it undertakes its constitutionally mandated responsibilities.But her emails.
name: Jim Himes

text: RT Yes, but did you hear about the house Dems trying to use gender neutral legislative language? The president sent a mob to Capitol Hill, now buildings are being evacuated and elected lawmakers are sheltering in their offices.
name: Jim Himes

text: RT Freshman GOP Congresswoman Just evacuated my office in Cannon due to a nearby threat. Now we’re seeing protesters assaulting Capitol Police. This is wrong. This is not who we are. I’m heartbroken for our nation today.
name: Jim Himes

text: The Congress will continue its work tonight, complete the count of the electoral college votes, defeat Republican objections, and confirm that Joe Biden is the next President and Kamala Harris is our next Vice President. Democracy wins. Thugs lose.
name: Brad Sherman

text: RT I have faced violent hatred before. I was not deterred then, and I will not be deterred now. Tonight, Congress will continue the business of certifying the electoral college votes.
name: Brad Sherman

text: I don’t know when the security situation in the Capitol will be resolved but my Democratic colleagues and I are ready to complete the process. As soon as the Capitol is secure, we should resume and we should complete our work.
name: Brad Sherman

text: Trump could end this attack on our capitol with one tweet. Instead he implicitly urges his supporters to occupy the capitol “peacefully “ and to disobey capitol police respectfully.
name: Brad Sherman

text: I never thought I’d tweet this: Today Senator Mitch McConnell gave an excellent speech.
name: Brad Sherman

text: The American people will not accept Trump and the violence he applauds. And the Republican Party can’t win without Trump’s most crazed supporters.
name: Brad Sherman

text: Today the party of Ronald Reagan died. Cause of death, suicide.
name: Brad Sherman

text: God Bless our Capitol Police officers and other law enforcement professionals working to restore order.
name: Sam Graves

text: Peaceful protests are protected by the Constitution, but this is not how we settle disputes in America.The violence and lawlessness happening at the United States Capitol right now is completely unacceptable and un-American. This is not what democracy looks like.
name: Sam Graves

text: Hi folks, my staff and I are safe. Thanks to the Capitol Police. A violent mob won’t stop us from upholding our constitutional duty to certify the election.This is a moment when everyone must decide whether our democracy is worth protecting.I believe it is.
name: Adam Schiff

text: Congress was once the place of giants.Have we become so small? Does our oath to uphold the Constitution, taken just days ago, mean so very little?I think not.It has never been our place to overturn an election.As long as we hope to remain a democracy, it never will be.
name: Adam Schiff

text: I am safe, and thank you to all who have reached out in concern. It's been a truly dark day at the U.S. Capitol. I was able to give Oregon reporters an update on the situation at the Capitol a short while ago. You can listen to the audio of my update here:
name: Jeff Merkley

text: Electoral college ballots rescued from the Senate floor. If our capable floor staff hadn’t grabbed them, they would have been burned by the mob.
name: Jeff Merkley

text: I am safe and was evacuated to a secure location almost immediately after defending the integrity of Arizona’s elections on the House Floor. Thank you for your concerns.
name: Raul Grijalva

text: Arizona Democrats aren’t buying the conspiracy theories of our Republican colleagues and President Trump. We’re about to speak on the House floor and protect the integrity of Arizona’s election and the will of the voters. Watch live. LIVE --> Joint Session of Congress: #ElectoralCollege Vote Certification
name: Raul Grijalva

text: We will return to the floor as soon as possible to finish certifying the results of the electoral college and declaring Joe Biden and Kamala Harris the next president and vice president of the United States.
name: Diana DeGette

text: Make no mistake: This was not a protest, it was an attempted coup. I never thought I’d see the day that our own president would attempt to bring down our government because he lost an election.
name: Diana DeGette

text: With our gas masks in hand, Rep. Scott Peters and I were briskly enroute from the Capitol to an undisclosed location.
name: Diana DeGette

text: We have been evacuated from the House chamber and moved to a safe location. This isn’t a protest. This is an attempted coup. I never thought we’d see such anarchy spurred by our own president.
name: Diana DeGette

text: We are locked down in the US Capitol because the president has instigated a riot to try to block us from certifying the election for his opponent. This is not who we are as Americans. We are so much better than this.
name: Diana DeGette

text: The violence that we are witnessing at the United States Capitol is completely unacceptable. I am thankful to the brave men and women of the who are doing their duty and working diligently to keep everyone in the Capitol safe. God bless our law enforcement.
name: Patrick McHenry

text: My statement on why I plan to certify:
name: Michael McCaul

text: Let me be clear, anyone who breached the Capitol today, or participated in the violence, should be arrested and prosecuted to the fullest extent of the law.
name: Michael McCaul

text: The violence and destruction we are witnessing in the Capitol is an assault on our democracy.
name: Michael McCaul

text: I like many people voted for President Trump in the 2020 election and hoped for a different result. But violence and destruction is not the way to express your grievances. This is disgraceful and has to end.
name: Michael McCaul

text: These unruly behaviors are completely unacceptable and place law enforcement and countless individuals in harm’s way.
name: Gus Bilirakis

text: My staff has been told to shelter in place for their safety, and I am watching the scene at the Capitol unfold. While I support the Constitutionally-protected right for peaceful protest, some of the images I am seeing on the news do not constitute a peaceful demonstration.
name: Gus Bilirakis

text: I tested positive for COVID-19 this morning, and as such, will not be on the House Floor for today’s debate. In accordance with CDC guidelines and upon the advice of the House Physician, I am in quarantine.
name: Gus Bilirakis

text: Trump has given us no choice. The 25th Amendment must be invoked NOW. We need to immediately wrest control of the country from him. He is not the commander of chief of the US. He is commander of chief of the Trump mob & proud boys. Pence must step up & defend our democracy.
name: Jackie Speier

text: We are in a safe place. I will have lots more to say about this. We are not a 3rd world country but you couldn’t tell that todaytoday.
name: Jackie Speier

text: The Capitol has been breeched. We are in lock down. Thank you, POTUS!
name: Jackie Speier

text: There’s an external threat outside. Speaker and majority leader escorted from the chamber
name: Jackie Speier

text: This debate should not even be taking place. The Constitution allows us ONLY to open the envelopes and count the votes.
name: Jackie Speier

text: The Constitution states: The President of the Senate shall, in the Presence of the Senate and House of Representatives, open all the Certificates, and the Votes shall then be counted. We can’t throw out the votes. For all the “originalists” how come this process isn’t illegal?
name: Jackie Speier

text: Harrowing moments inside the US Capitol!!! Hats off to the Capitol Hill Police protecting us. We are safe and secure. Pray for our nation.
name: Hank Johnson

text: I pray that law enforcement continues to use great strength and confidence in restoring law and order across Washington. In the great words of Abraham Lincoln, “A house divided against itself, cannot stand.". We must unite together, as Americans.
name: Pete Sessions

text: Today, there was an illegal and unprecedented charge on the U.S. Capitol. It should not have occurred and should not be tolerated. My staff and I are safe. I sincerely appreciate all the calls and concern for our safety here in the nation’s capital.
name: Pete Sessions

text: My staff and I are safe. Thank you to all law enforcement for protecting us. I am praying for every officer's safety.
name: Pete Sessions

text: I am safe.
name: Jan Schakowsky

text: Carrying Trump flags.
name: Eleanor Holmes Norton

text: During a dangerous & frightening situation, I am incredibly grateful for the diligence & bravery of law enforcement, including the U.S. Capitol Police, risking their lives to keep members & staff safe.
name: Tom Cole

text: Such shameful behavior runs contrary to upholding and respecting the constitutional rule of law & threatens the preservation of our great Republic. This is not the American way.
name: Tom Cole

text: I am outraged by the lawless protests that unfolded at the U.S. Capitol today. While Americans have the right to passionately voice their views & peacefully dissent in protest, I strongly condemn the perpetrators of this destructive & violent activity.
name: Tom Cole

text: Call it what it is: An attack on the Capitol is an attack on democracy. Today we are trying to use the democratic process to address grievances. This violence inhibits our ability to do that. Violent protests were unacceptable this summer and are unacceptable now.
name: Cynthia M. Lummis

text: The First Amendment only protects peaceful assembly. Stop the Violence. United States Capitol Police saved my life.Attacks on law enforcement officers trying to do their jobs are never acceptable. Period.We can passionately protest without being violent.
name: Cynthia M. Lummis

text: Update: I am safe and sheltered, but utterly devastated by today’s events.
name: Gregory Meeks

text: RT All of this was predictable. It was predicted. And the lasting shame of history will be on all those who refused to act out of cowardice, ambition, or their own allegiance to an authoritarian movement.
name: Gregory Meeks

text: RT US standing in the world - its defense of democracy, rule of law and peaceful transitions of power - preached and encouraged for generations - has plunged to a disturbing low today.
name: Gregory Meeks

text: The world is watching as the greatest democracy braces against an attempted coup, stirred by its leader who’d rather watch the country burn than transition power. Our ability to advocate for democracy around the world will be significantly hurt after this tragic day in America.
name: Gregory Meeks

text: A woman is dead! The U.S. Capitol is under siege. Peaceful transfer of power has been disrupted. Trump has incited this chaos & violence. The 25th amendment must be invoked. If not, Congress must impeach & convict Trump.13 days is far too long for Trump to remain in office.
name: Gwen Moore

text: I am safe and sheltered but this is an incredibly disturbing and shameful moment for our country that was encouraged by the POTUS.
name: Gwen Moore

text: I condemn the actions of everyone participating in the mob violence at the Capitol today. We must restore law and order.
name: Ken Calvert

text: The protestors disrupting the constitutional process right now must back down and let Congress do their job. This is no way to express their disappointment in the election process. Violence is never acceptable.
name: Ken Calvert

text: My staff and I are currently safe. This is a dark day for America.
name: Jim Cooper

text: The violence we saw today is totally inexcusable. Nothing justifies it, and I condemn it in the strongest way possible. Everyone protesting in the Capitol should leave immediately.
name: Darrell Issa

text: To all protesting at the Capitol: It is time to disperse in a safe and orderly manner. Please support the Capitol Police, local law enforcement, and the National Guard. Help others to do the same.
name: Darrell Issa

text: Please people; no violence. That only hurts our cause. Those leading the charge like the guy in yellow with the communist hammer & sickle tattoo: stopping the violence applies to you too.
name: Louie Gohmert

text: Donald Trump is responsible for today's coup at the Capitol and the attack on our government and democracy. He is a direct threat to our country. He needs to be impeached, removed from office, and barred from ever holding office again.
name: Ed Markey

text: As soon as the Capitol is secure, Congress must cast our votes affirming the results of the Electoral College so that Joe Biden and Kamala Harris are sworn in January 20. This is how we respond to this assault on our democracy. By reaffirming it. Democracy will prevail.
name: Ed Markey

text: An update. I and my staff are safe, sheltering in place, and following the guidance and protocols of Capitol Police.
name: Ed Markey

text: The events unfolding at the Capitol are shameful. There is no justification for violence and destruction. It has to stop now. This is not who we are as a nation. Thank you to the Capitol Police who are keeping us safe.
name: Roy Blunt

text: Today is a very dark day for our country. I am safe thanks to the protection and swift action by our law enforcement officials. Our Founding Fathers warned against mob rule. Law and order must be established and maintained.
name: Richard Shelby

text: This only strengthens our resolve to get the Electoral Votes counted & certified and continue with a peaceful transition of power, as has been a hallmark of our nation. It’s time to get back to the business of the people & of the country as we build a better future.
name: Ed Perlmutter

text: I’m safe, but I'm filled w/sadness & anger as we witness these protests. It's the result of a fever that has been building for weeks, months & years, and which has only been further incited by President Trump. Today is a point of inflection & reflection, & we need to say enough.
name: Ed Perlmutter

text: The NDAA & $2k payments are two different bills. I have long supported increasing the amount of direct payments for hardworking families & I look forward to working with a new administration to provide the support that families, businesses and communities need in the coming year.
name: Ed Perlmutter

text: Let me be very clear, Trump must shoulder the blame of this tragic day. His lack of respect and dangerous rhetoric have caused this. The National Guard and law enforcement must disperse them as soon as possible and they must be prosecuted to the fullest extent of the law.
name: Kurt Schrader

text: I am witnessing something I never thought I would see in my lifetime. Looking out the window, I see Americans destroying their own Capitol. These are not “protestors” they are a violent mob of terrorists hellbent on destroying our Republic.
name: Kurt Schrader

text: My staff and I are in an undisclosed safe location.
name: Kurt Schrader

text: What’s happening now in the U.S. Capitol is sickening and unacceptable. Guns drawn inside the House chamber and reports of shots fired and one woman in critical condition make this a dark day in the history of our nation.
name: Vern Buchanan

text: Checked in with several constituents here in D.C. for the rally. They are protesting peacefully on the Nat’l Mall & supporting law enforcement while making their voices known.THAT’s how you do it in America. The violence must end.
name: Kevin Brady

text: Thank you for defending the Constitution, as difficult as it may be in these times. Throughout the years I’ve known you, you’ve always been a man of principle & a constitutional conservative.
name: Kevin Brady

text: RT Thank you to Capitol Police for protecting the People's House.Protesters have a Constitutionally-protected right to be heard, but I urge them to remain peaceful.
name: Kevin Brady

text: What is unfolding is unacceptable and un-American. It has got to stop.
name: Kevin McCarthy

text: RT Rep. Kevin McCarthy :"What we are currently watching unfold is un-American. I am disappointed. I am sad. This is not what our country should look like."
name: Kevin McCarthy

text: RT . responds to the breach of the Capitol:"This is so un-American... I could not be sadder or more disappointed at the way our country looks at this very moment...This is not the American way. This is not protected by the First Amendment. This must stop now."
name: Kevin McCarthy

text: The lawlessness and violence on Capitol Hill today was a dangerous, shameful, and outrageous attack on our democracy. But this attack will not deter Congress from performing our constitutional duty. We will affirm the certified results of the presidential election.
name: Susan Collins

text: Thank you to all of the New Mexicans who have reached out to my office. My staff and I are safe and sheltering in place.I also want to thank our Capitol police officers who have bravely protected Members of Congress. I ask that you join me in praying for their safety.
name: Ben Ray Lujan

text: What we’ve witnessed today is an insurrection and attack on our democracy.When it is safe to do so, I will return to the Senate chamber and get back to work to defend the U.S. Constitution.
name: Ben Ray Lujan

text: RT I will vote to respect the American people’s decision and defend our system of government. My full remarks:
name: Mitch McConnell

text: The right to protest peacefully is protected under the Constitution but the actions by violent mobs against our law enforcement and property at the building today are not. should condemn this unacceptable vandalism and violence.
name: Rob Portman

text: RT Watch my interviews with and about the #chaosattheCapitol and their thoughts about
name: Jim Langevin

text: Going live on shortly to discuss the ongoing situation in the Capitol.
name: Jim Langevin

text: This disgraceful attack on the Capitol will not deter us. Congress should fulfill its constitutional duty and count the Electoral College votes tonight. We will honor the choice of the people. Joe Biden will be our President.
name: Jim Langevin

text: RT WATCH: "This is not just a protest - this is a coup attempt," told us at the top of our 4pm newscastLangevin was in his Capitol Hill office, where he is in lockdown with his staff
name: Jim Langevin

text: My staff and I are safe for the moment. I am deeply saddened by the turn of events. It did not have to be this way.
name: Jim Langevin

text: If we can do so safely and without further danger to police, we should continue with the congressional proceedings tonight—to show the true strength of Democracy in America.
name: Jeff Fortenberry

text: Thank you to everyone asking if I am safe. This remains a tense, volatile situation. Good people who came to peacefully march—get away from here. It’s not safe. To the fools who are entering the Capitol—you are undermining the principles of rightful justice and democracy.
name: Jeff Fortenberry

text: Today in DC should have been about meaningful debate, peaceful protest and the Rule of Law -- not chaos and talks of coups. I unequivocally condemn any violence and criminal acts taking place, and pray for a restoration of peace.
name: Scott Perry

text: There must be legal consequences for what happened today.
name: Albio Sires

text: The world was watching the symbol of democracy, our country’s Capitol, as insurrectionists stormed the building. We are fortunate that after four years President Trump has not succeeded in taking down our institutions of democracy, but he has come precipitously close.
name: Albio Sires

text: I am sickened by today’s events. The world was watching as a sitting American president attempted to takedown democracy by inciting chaos and violence, because he cannot accept that he lost an election.
name: Albio Sires

text: My staff and I are safe and grateful for the protection of the Capitol Police.
name: Albio Sires

text: The violence and lawlessness of rioters at the Capitol right now is one of the gravest assaults on our democracy in memory. If this was happening in any other country we would be calling it a coup attempt.
name: Albio Sires

text: We are now back in recess.
name: Albio Sires

text: Debate has resumed. I and other members who were on the floor were addressed by Capitol Police and locked down in the Chamber because security at the Capitol has been breached.
name: Albio Sires

text: I know our institutions are strong enough to withstand these attacks, and it is all too clear that we must pass democratic reforms to ensure the erosion of our norms and democratic processes does not happen again.
name: Albio Sires

text: What we are seeing is members of the GOP trying to dismiss the legitimate votes of millions of Americans, and subvert democracy. These are not the actions of democratic leaders, but of autocrats.
name: Albio Sires

text: “Siento lágrimas por nuestra democracia. El mundo mira hacia EE.UU. como el faro de luz de la democracia y el respeto de derechos humanos...y lo que vimos hoy es anarquía, no democracia”.Vea mi entrevista con y sobre los disturbios en el Capitolio. 👇
name: Bob Menendez

text: “Yo he pasado mi vida hablando en contra de este tipo de actuaciones en distintas partes del mundo. Nunca pensé que veríamos esto en los Estados Unidos”. Vea mi entrevista con y sobre los disturbios de hoy en el Capitolio. 👇
name: Bob Menendez

text: Al momento, mi equipo y yo estamos seguros y siguiendo las instrucciones de la policía del Capitolio.La escena en el Capitolio va en contra de todos los valores que hemos jurado defender. Nuestra democracia prevalecerá.
name: Bob Menendez

text: My staff and I are safe and following guidance from Capitol Police.The scene in the Capitol goes against every value we pledge to uphold as a nation. Democracy will prevail.
name: Bob Menendez

text: I condemn the violence and destruction at the U.S. Capitol in the strongest possible terms. It is completely unacceptable and unpatriotic. God Bless the & our law enforcement officers. Please pray for our nation.
name: Jerry Moran

text: Americans support peaceful protests, First Amendment activity, and the men and women of law enforcement. What happened today is wrong and is not what America is about.
name: Jim Jordan

text: Stop the violence. Support Capitol Police.
name: Jim Jordan

text: RT
name: Jim Jordan

text: Hard to take seriously the political arsonists, starting with Trump, when they say they want to put out the flames after they lit the match. I never thought we would live to see the day that violent mobs seized control of the Capitol. I cry for our country.
name: Chris Van Hollen

text: My prayers are with the officers that are protecting and defending and who have gone down. Mr. President, tell your supporters to stop the violence. Stop the assault. Now.
name: Lisa Murkowski

text: The dangerous destructive activity at the Capitol is continuing to unfold. I, along with other members of the Senate, are secure but the situation is clearly not safe. It is truly mob rule at the moment.
name: Lisa Murkowski

text: Peaceful protests are a fundamental right in the United States, but violence is absolutely unacceptable. Respect our law enforcement officers’ orders. Vacate the Capitol and let the process unfold. Anyone committing violent acts should be immediately arrested.
name: John Carter

text: Stop these attacks on Capitol Police who serve to protect the People's House. Protesting peacefully is your right. Violence, aggression, and breaching security perimeters are not. Stop this now.
name: Cathy McMorris Rodgers

text: From and me:We are calling on President Trump to demand that all protestors leave the U.S. Capitol and Capitol Grounds immediately.
name: Chuck Schumer

text: It's a little late for that. Don't you think?
name: Chuck Schumer

text: I am safe. Members of my staff are safe.The protestors within the Capitol must immediately back down. Senseless violence accomplishes absolutely nothing.Law and order must be upheld.
name: Virginia Foxx

text: Violence like what we’re witnessing in the United States Capitol is unacceptable.People have the right to peacefully protest, and there is absolutely no reason to resort to destruction.God bless the brave men and women of the United States Capitol Police for protecting us.
name: Virginia Foxx

text: . and I are calling on President Trump to demand that all protestors leave the U.S. Capitol and Capitol grounds immediately.
name: Nancy Pelosi

text: I want to thank Capitol Police for their bravery and for keeping those on Capitol grounds safe. Violence is never an acceptable answer.
name: Michael C. Burgess

text: My statement on today's attacks on the Capitol and the joint meeting of Congress on counting the votes of the Electoral College ⤵️
name: Bob Latta

text: These attacks on our democracy, Capitol, & are abhorrent & must stop. This is not how the Constitution has guided our country & citizens over the past 232yrs. My eternal gratitude goes to the men & women who protect us 24/7 at the Capitol. I pray for their safety.
name: Bob Latta

text: legislative body. Thoughtful deliberation is at the heart of our Republic and ensuring the peaceful transition of power is at the very bulwark of our democracy. I want Congress continuing that tradition and upholding that duty.
name: Rob Wittman

text: peaceful disagreement – not anarchy and violence. Today, Congress began the solemn work to certify the Presidential election; and that debate should continue within the established bounds envisioned by our Founders and previously practiced by this
name: Rob Wittman

text: Protests are a right, but must remain peaceful. I am deeply concerned and call for the immediate end of the unrest, rioting, and vandalism taking place at the Capitol. Please go home and allow us to finish the work of the people through the great American tradition of
name: Rob Wittman

text: Objecting is a procedural term, meaning debate can occur. I have been clear from the beginning I fully support debating and examining all evidence in states where Constitutional qs have been raised. I want to get back to work. I want to hear the debates so we can move forward.
name: Rob Wittman

text: RT What is unfolding is unacceptable and un-American. It has got to stop.
name: Rob Wittman

text: Quentin, that's not true. I was going into today ready to hear open debate with an open mind. What we are seeing now, this is not America.
name: Rob Wittman

text: David, that's not true. I was going into today ready to hear open debate with an open mind. What we are seeing now, this is not America.
name: Rob Wittman

text: This is absolutely unacceptable. This is not how we conduct the Nation's business. Please allow us to get the work of the people completed.
name: Rob Wittman

text: RT Thank you to Capitol Police for protecting the People's House.Protesters have a Constitutionally-protected right to be heard, but I urge them to remain peaceful.
name: Rob Wittman

text: I am very fortunate to be sheltering in a safe location on the hill.
name: Chellie Pingree

text: Office buildings in the Capitol complex have been evacuated. This unprecedented lawlessness was incited by our outgoing President because he is determined to undermine the peaceful transfer of power. Trump protesters have broken through barriers at the US Capitol
name: Chellie Pingree

text: Thanks to everyone for reaching out. I am safe. In lockdown.This is not ok. We are a nation of laws. Please pray for all of our law enforcement, elected officials and staff on Capitol Hill. Please pray for our country.
name: Tim Ryan

text: This is political theater and that’s it.The people’s voices were heard in November, the states have certified the results, and will be seated as the next POTUS.
name: Tim Ryan

text: RT The Sergeant-at- Arms has announced the U.S. Capitol is secure, per
name: John Cornyn

text: RT I have spoken with members of the Senate. They want to return to America’s Senate chamber and conduct the people’s business. This desire is in the finest tradition of our Republic. God bless the Congress.
name: John Cornyn

text: RT Announcement just went out at the Capitol on the loudspeakers that everyone must leave the Capitol grounds or be subject to arrest
name: John Cornyn

text: I condemn any kind of violence and intimidation. This is unacceptable.
name: Steve Daines

text: Today’s violent attack on the U.S. Capitol was an attack on American democracy itself. I condemn today’s violence in the strongest terms & perpetrators deserve to be prosecuted to the fullest extent of the law. I also thank Capitol Police for protecting our Capitol & staff
name: Chuck Grassley

text: Thanks for your concern — I am safe and sheltering in place with other senators. Please join me in praying for our country, and for our fellow Americans to do the right thing.
name: Mark Warner

text: My staff and I are safe and grateful to all law enforcement for risking their safety to protect us. This violence and disrespect for our Constitution and our republic is unacceptable and must stop now.
name: Jim Inhofe

text: The violence and destruction taking place at the Capitol are unacceptable and must cease.
name: John Boozman

text: Peaceful protest is a constitutionally guaranteed right and that right must be protected for all Americans. Violence is unacceptable. United States Capitol Police saved my life.Attacks on law enforcement officers trying to do their jobs are never acceptable. Period.We can passionately protest without being violent.
name: Thomas Tiffany
